cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the training of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and investigates the underlying factors that lead to their success or failure. It also proposes a solution to make the gradient of the optimal discriminative function reliable, which is a fundamental problem in GAN training. 

It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as GANs are widely used in image generation and manipulation tasks. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as GANs are a popular application of AI and the paper proposes a new approach to improve their performance. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category as GANs are a type of neural network and the paper deals with their training. 

Finally, cs.GR (Graphics) could also be a relevant category as GANs are used for generating realistic images and the paper proposes a new approach to improve their quality.
